<font color="#FF0000">SEMI-TRUE ACCOUNT</font><br>
<tt>Mon Aug 25 20:51:22 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I didn't eat in Viet Nam!<br>
I didn't sleep in Viet Nam!<br>
I didn't bathe or take showers in Viet Nam!<br><br>
The only reason I carried a P-38... was to clean the blood from beneath my fingernails!<br><br>
I DON'T PLAY!!!  I quit school because they had recess.<br><br>
Only time I ever saw C-rations was when I was on R&amp;R... and at Christmas.<br><br>
Ate a lot of snakes (carried them on board my chopper)...didn't know that you were supposed to kill, clean, and cook them first... But that was in Cambodia and that is another story.<br><br>
Had trouble writing my own name with a large crayon... but with four mounted M-60 flex guns I could do a provincal census in one pass... with one finger... with one eye closed.<br><br>
I am entered into the M-60 Hall of Fame... Jarheads utter my name in awe... (of course Marines utter every word with awe.. i.e. Hitchhiking Marine, &quot;Awe you going my way?... disappointed Marine, &quot;Awe Shit!&quot; or a Marine being questioned, &quot;Awe don't know, Sir!&quot; or a Marine seeing a flush toilet for the first time, &quot;Awe be damned!&quot;<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
